# Lab 01 - Identify PC Hardware Components

## Objective
Identify and understand the function of core internal computer hardware components.

## Lab Environment
- Personally built computer
- Pc Building Simulator

## Components identified

### 1. Central Processing Unit(CPU)
- This is the "brain" of the computer
- Executes instructions and processes data

### 2. Random Access Memory(RAM)
-  Temporary memory used for active tasks
- Volatile(Data is lost when power is off)

### 3. Storage(SSD/HDD)
- Permanent data storage
- Hard Disk Drive(HDD): Mechanical and slower
- Solid State Drive(SSD): Faster, no moving parts

###4. Motherboard
- Main circuit board connecting all components
- Communication between all components begins here

### 5. Power Supply Unit(PSU)
- Converts AC(Alternating Current) to DC(Direct Current)
- Converts wall electricity to usable power for the components

### 6. Graphics Processing Unit(GPU)
- Handles graphics and video rendering
- Can be integrated with the CPU or be a dedicated card

## Steps Performed
1. Observed internal components of computer physically and digitally(PC Building Simulator)
2. Identified each major hardware component
3. Researched the function of each component 
4. Structured components within the computer
5. Documented findings

## Results
- Successfully identified all major internal PC components and  understood their roles in system operations.

## Issues encountered
Remembering to keep track of screws, luckily parts come with extras

## Key Takeaways
- Each hardware component has a specific role in the system performance
- Understanding hardware is essential for troubleshooting and upgrades

